            <person xml:id="pers1682">
               <p>A native of <placeName>Scotland</placeName> who lived for a brief period in
                     <placeName>South Carolina</placeName>, Rankin returned to
                     <placeName>Britain</placeName>, where he was converted under the influence of
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2221.xml"/>Whitefield</persName> and
                  other evangelical preachers. He began preaching independently in <date when="1759"
                     >1759</date>, and became a <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg>
                  within <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s
                  connexion in <date when="1761">1761</date>. From <date from="1773" to="1778"
                     >1773–78</date> he was back in <placeName>North America</placeName> as
                  &apos;general superintendent&apos; of the lay preachers <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> appointed to this realm. He
                  completed his career back in <placeName>London</placeName>. See <hi rend="italic"
                     >DEB</hi>, 916; <hi rend="italic">EMP</hi>, 5:135–217; and Vickers, <hi
                     rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 288.</p>
            </person>
